1
00:01:25,170 --> 00:01:32,030
[Echoes of a Thousand Moons]

2
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:35,000
[Episode 1]

3
00:01:38,940 --> 00:01:40,000
[People's Republic of China]

4
00:01:39,080 --> 00:01:40,479
Dear Yueming,

5
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,620
[The Founding Ceremony
of the People's Republic of China]

6
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,490
I've read the letter

7
00:01:42,509 --> 00:01:44,370
you sent from Beijing many times.

8
00:01:44,770 --> 00:01:46,000
You witnessed

9
00:01:46,030 --> 00:01:48,370
the founding
of New China with your own eyes,

10
00:01:48,370 --> 00:01:50,170
and saw everyone

11
00:01:50,190 --> 00:01:51,950
smiling so happily.

12
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:55,610
You said your teacher assigned an essay

13
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:57,960
titled "My Country, My Home,"

14
00:01:58,289 --> 00:02:00,820
and you wanted
to hear the story of our family.

15
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:04,850
Where should I begin?

16
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:06,520
Yueming,

17
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:07,440
as you know,

18
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:08,960
you have two fathers.

19
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,770
One gave you life,

20
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:13,080
and the other

21
00:02:13,450 --> 00:02:15,400
protected you with his life.

22
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,050
You also know

23
00:02:17,450 --> 00:02:19,140
that on the day you were born,

24
00:02:19,170 --> 00:02:22,680
China fell into its darkest night.

25
00:02:24,079 --> 00:02:27,020
You experienced a little of that history,

26
00:02:27,070 --> 00:02:30,400
but there are still many parts
you have not heard of.

27
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:34,280
I have the responsibility to tell you

28
00:02:34,850 --> 00:02:36,930
this history exactly as it happened.

29
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:39,050
The journey of our family

30
00:02:39,050 --> 00:02:40,800
has been bound to the nation—

31
00:02:41,050 --> 00:02:42,800
from the darkest night,

32
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:45,930
we made our way
step by step into the light of dawn.

33
00:02:46,610 --> 00:02:50,079
This long story of thousands of miles

34
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:54,530
[Marco Polo Bridge Incident, 1994]

35
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,450
begins in the spring of 1944,

36
00:02:52,450 --> 00:02:56,400
-when the first light appeared.
-Folks!

37
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,620
Hurry up!

38
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,010
We are currently positioned here.

39
00:03:22,010 --> 00:03:23,610
The enemy may pass through this area,

40
00:03:23,610 --> 00:03:24,640
so we can deploy our troops here.

41
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:26,760
-Regimental Commander!
-This position.

42
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:28,560
I, Meng Wanfu, am here to report!

43
00:03:32,770 --> 00:03:33,840
Meng Wanfu.

44
00:03:36,780 --> 00:03:37,579
Take the guns.

45
00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:38,850
Here.

46
00:03:38,990 --> 00:03:39,850
Give them to me.

47
00:03:44,090 --> 00:03:45,000
Brother.

48
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:50,730
Regimental Commander,
I have returned to the unit.

49
00:03:48,130 --> 00:03:50,530
[Meng Wanfu]

50
00:03:50,870 --> 00:03:52,760
[7th Subdistrict, Suzhong Military Region,
New Fourth Army]

51
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,450
Brigade Commander, Regimental Commander.

52
00:03:52,780 --> 00:03:54,290
[Zhang Yunkui, Regimental Commander
of Independent Regiment]

53
00:03:55,050 --> 00:03:57,490
Zhang Dougui, Zhang Yunkui.

54
00:03:59,210 --> 00:04:01,610
Kong Erbao, He Bishi,

55
00:04:02,050 --> 00:04:05,080
Zhang Yunkui, Meng Wanfu.

56
00:04:07,010 --> 00:04:08,610
It feels like a 7-year dream.

57
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,960
Yes, it's like a dream.

58
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:17,290
[Nanjing, August 1937]

59
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:14,460
Yueming,

60
00:04:14,670 --> 00:04:16,610
in the summer of 1937,

61
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:18,709
you were still in my womb.

62
00:04:19,140 --> 00:04:21,170
At that time, the War
of Resistance Against Japanese Aggression

63
00:04:21,170 --> 00:04:23,200
had just fully broken out.

64
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:24,660
[Zhang's Mansion]

65
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:25,290
The Communist Party of China called for

66
00:04:25,290 --> 00:04:28,010
the establishment
of an anti-Japanese national united front,

67
00:04:28,010 --> 00:04:31,970
emphasizing the mobilization of
all national forces to resist aggression.

68
00:04:31,970 --> 00:04:35,090
The Chinese nation united as never before.

69
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:38,530
The Nationalist Government
also made military deployments.

70
00:04:38,530 --> 00:04:39,970
Your father Yunkui

71
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,480
hadn't been home for several months.

72
00:05:14,370 --> 00:05:21,480
[Ding Yujiao]

73
00:05:18,150 --> 00:05:20,300
Mrs. Liu, did you hear that?

74
00:05:27,570 --> 00:05:30,130
[Zhang's Mansion]

75
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,000
Yi!

76
00:05:50,290 --> 00:05:51,240
The Young Master is back!

77
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:51,700
Really?

78
00:05:51,850 --> 00:05:52,560
Hurry.

79
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:54,050
I need to make some of
the Young Master's favorite food.

80
00:05:54,050 --> 00:05:54,650
Hurry up!

81
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,390
Okay!

82
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:07,240
Father,

83
00:06:07,710 --> 00:06:08,630
I'm back.

84
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:20,760
[Zhang Ruxian]

85
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:22,410
Compared to Yan Zhenqing, what is

86
00:06:23,490 --> 00:06:25,200
Zhao Mengfu lacking?

87
00:06:25,630 --> 00:06:27,650
[187th Division,
National Revolutionary Army]

88
00:06:25,850 --> 00:06:27,170
My calligraphy isn't very good.

89
00:06:27,170 --> 00:06:29,090
I only know that a person's character
determines the value of their calligraphy.

90
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:29,800
[Zhang Yunkui,
Brigade Commander of the 87th Brigade]

91
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,970
Zhao Mengfu lacks unwavering integrity.

92
00:06:31,970 --> 00:06:34,409
That's what Kang Youwei and his ilk say.

93
00:06:35,050 --> 00:06:38,090
"Do not follow the decadent ways
of the Zhao and Dong types."

94
00:06:38,090 --> 00:06:39,420
The words aren't wrong.

95
00:06:39,530 --> 00:06:42,170
But what did Kang Youwei know
about calligraphy?

96
00:06:42,170 --> 00:06:43,680
Such grand words!

97
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:46,680
Yes. Please teach me, Father.

98
00:06:46,970 --> 00:06:48,490
Zhao Mengfu was talented.

99
00:06:51,580 --> 00:06:52,760
A talented person

100
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:55,050
can protect themselves

101
00:06:55,610 --> 00:06:58,170
and those around them.

102
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:00,140
A person of great talent

103
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,560
can preserve the cultural lineage.

104
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:07,050
But Yan Zhenqing had integrity.

105
00:07:07,490 --> 00:07:08,170
Talent and integrity,

106
00:07:08,170 --> 00:07:10,410
the two words are worlds apart.

107
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:13,420
From beginning to end, Yan Zhenqing wrote

108
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:16,610
with the tip of his brush held at the center,
vigorous and independent,

109
00:07:16,610 --> 00:07:18,560
sharp and unyielding,

110
00:07:18,610 --> 00:07:20,290
intending to convey to the world

111
00:07:20,290 --> 00:07:22,800
the meaning of "manhood".

112
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:26,320
So although he had no intention
of becoming a calligrapher,

113
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:31,050
he was revered as a master
for all generations.

114
00:07:31,830 --> 00:07:32,830
I understood.

115
00:07:34,490 --> 00:07:36,170
Why did you come back today?

116
00:07:36,290 --> 00:07:38,409
I was appointed as the major brigade commander
of the 87th Brigade.

117
00:07:38,409 --> 00:07:39,409
I need to rush to Shanghai immediately

118
00:07:39,409 --> 00:07:40,670
to prepare for battle.

119
00:08:18,550 --> 00:08:20,090
The Nationalist Government,

120
00:08:20,090 --> 00:08:21,680
even at this stage,

121
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:25,100
still pins its hopes
on international mediation,

122
00:08:25,470 --> 00:08:27,270
leaving things to chance.

123
00:08:27,290 --> 00:08:28,490
It's not advisable.

124
00:08:28,860 --> 00:08:30,530
The September 18 Incident in the Northeast

125
00:08:30,530 --> 00:08:32,220
and what happened in Shanghai 5 years ago—

126
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:34,320
haven't we suffered enough losses?

127
00:08:34,650 --> 00:08:36,220
On the contrary, the Communist Party's

128
00:08:36,220 --> 00:08:37,799
"August 1st Declaration"

129
00:08:37,890 --> 00:08:39,500
is more visionary.

130
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:41,179
Have you read it?

131
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:42,200
I have, Father.

132
00:08:42,659 --> 00:08:44,490
They call on the entire nation
to carry out the war of resistance

133
00:08:44,490 --> 00:08:45,490
and defend against foreign aggression.

134
00:08:44,590 --> 00:08:48,810
[The Gentleman Is Not a Vessel]

135
00:08:45,830 --> 00:08:47,410
It inspired me greatly.

136
00:08:47,430 --> 00:08:48,960
I also agree with this idea.

137
00:08:49,550 --> 00:08:51,080
You are absolutely right.

138
00:08:51,290 --> 00:08:53,540
If we unite the national united front,

139
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,080
resist aggression,

140
00:08:55,130 --> 00:08:56,330
take the initiative,

141
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:59,650
and push the Japanese forces
out of the Huangpu River,

142
00:08:59,650 --> 00:09:01,510
how could we not achieve victory?

143
00:09:02,010 --> 00:09:04,010
How could the enemy not be defeated?

144
00:09:04,370 --> 00:09:06,130
Then again,

145
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:09,080
how can we be sure of victory?

146
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:11,960
Being fearless is already enough.

147
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:13,890
So,

148
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:16,090
we still need to cultivate our spirit.

149
00:09:16,180 --> 00:09:17,440
You are right, Father.

150
00:09:18,780 --> 00:09:19,260
Come.

151
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:28,730
Coming!

152
00:09:31,930 --> 00:09:33,740
Come on, Buns, serve the dishes.

153
00:09:33,770 --> 00:09:34,770
Coming!

154
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:39,010
Flavored eggplant!

155
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:40,520
Here we go!

156
00:10:00,990 --> 00:10:01,680
Brother.

157
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:04,720
Nothing lifts the spirits
like a happy occasion.

158
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,080
You are a bridegroom now.

159
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,990
Your smile reaches your ears.

160
00:10:08,250 --> 00:10:08,980
Buns.

161
00:10:09,450 --> 00:10:11,180
I'll just ask you one question.

162
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:12,730
How do I look?

163
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,650
My brother is a human.

164
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:17,280
What do you know?

165
00:10:17,430 --> 00:10:19,590
All that glitters

166
00:10:20,290 --> 00:10:21,800
is not gold.

167
00:10:21,830 --> 00:10:22,800
For a person,

168
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:25,220
the most important thing is just 2 words.

169
00:10:25,270 --> 00:10:26,000
What?

170
00:10:26,020 --> 00:10:27,620
Food and clothing.

171
00:10:28,180 --> 00:10:29,060
Brothers!

172
00:10:30,010 --> 00:10:31,110
What about one word?

173
00:10:31,110 --> 00:10:32,640
Food!

174
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:33,460
Bah!

175
00:10:33,530 --> 00:10:34,560
It's money!

176
00:10:36,290 --> 00:10:37,810
Sir.

177
00:10:38,650 --> 00:10:40,530
We are going to the battlefield tomorrow.

178
00:10:40,530 --> 00:10:41,360
Yes, yes.

179
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,180
We just want some meat today!

180
00:10:43,250 --> 00:10:43,930
Meat.

181
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,420
You just gave us this?

182
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,290
Sir, let me explain.

183
00:10:48,370 --> 00:10:49,370
Now the price of meat

184
00:10:49,370 --> 00:10:50,680
changes every day.

185
00:10:50,710 --> 00:10:52,090
It's rising faster

186
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,410
than

187
00:10:53,410 --> 00:10:54,290
Japanese planes!

188
00:10:54,290 --> 00:10:56,770
And the key is that
there is nowhere to buy it.

189
00:10:56,730 --> 00:10:57,430
[87th Brigade,
National Revolutionary Army]

190
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:57,600
I'm telling you.

191
00:10:57,460 --> 00:10:58,570
[Wang Zhengxin,
Platoon Leader of the 806th Regiment]

192
00:10:58,050 --> 00:10:58,800
Four eggs.

193
00:10:58,930 --> 00:11:00,800
I'll make some egg soup

194
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:02,130
for you four gentlemen.

195
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:04,010
With extra wood ear mushrooms
and vermicelli!

196
00:11:04,010 --> 00:11:04,560
Extra...

197
00:11:06,010 --> 00:11:07,170
You look down on us, don't you?

198
00:11:07,170 --> 00:11:07,800
No. No.

199
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:08,840
No, sir.

200
00:11:08,930 --> 00:11:09,480
Listen to me.

201
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:11,130
We risk our lives

202
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:12,110
to defend our country.

203
00:11:12,110 --> 00:11:12,850
Who are we doing this for?

204
00:11:12,850 --> 00:11:13,580
Who?

205
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,410
For you!

206
00:11:14,530 --> 00:11:15,840
Yes, for me.

207
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:18,280
-All you think is money, huh?
-No, no, no.

208
00:11:17,420 --> 00:11:19,000
[87th Brigade,
National Revolutionary Army]

209
00:11:18,310 --> 00:11:19,200
Cut the crap.

210
00:11:19,020 --> 00:11:20,510
[Yu Yuansheng,
Company Commander of 806th Regiment]

211
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:19,720
Beef.

212
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:20,890
Do you have it or not?

213
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,530
Sir,

214
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:23,680
we really don't have it.

215
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:24,250
Really?

216
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:25,330
Really!

217
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:27,080
I wouldn't dare lie!

218
00:11:30,650 --> 00:11:31,710
What are you doing?

219
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:33,250
Sir!

220
00:11:33,290 --> 00:11:33,910
Brothers!

221
00:11:33,930 --> 00:11:34,330
Don't!

222
00:11:34,410 --> 00:11:35,560
We're eating meat today.

223
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:37,770
Pork belly or ribs?

224
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,410
Why don't you choose?

225
00:11:38,410 --> 00:11:39,170
Don't!

226
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:42,210
Don't waste time with him!
Smash the restaurant!

227
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:45,290
Chinese don't fight Chinese!

228
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:47,530
Sirs! Sirs!

229
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:48,250
Sirs.

230
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:49,080
Calm down.

231
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:49,800
Calm down.

232
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:51,040
Let's not fight.

233
00:11:51,060 --> 00:11:51,830
Let's not fight.

234
00:11:51,830 --> 00:11:52,440
Calm down.

235
00:11:52,470 --> 00:11:53,550
Calm down.

236
00:11:53,570 --> 00:11:54,290
Calm down.

237
00:11:56,810 --> 00:11:58,650
-Sir, please spare my life!
-Sir, sir.

238
00:11:58,650 --> 00:12:00,040
-Please calm down. Please spare my life!
-Calm down.

239
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:00,810
Calm down.

240
00:12:01,050 --> 00:12:01,990
Please calm down.

241
00:12:01,990 --> 00:12:02,830
Here.

242
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,080
Have a cigarette.

243
00:12:06,070 --> 00:12:06,720
Have a cigarette.

244
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:08,250
-Yeah, have a cigarette.
-Have a cigarette.

245
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:09,250
Have a cigarette.

246
00:12:09,250 --> 00:12:10,370
Sir,

247
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:12,010
here. Have a cigarette.

248
00:12:12,050 --> 00:12:12,680
Have a cigarette.

249
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:14,060
Here, calm down.

250
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:16,220
Sir, have a cigarette.

251
00:12:17,530 --> 00:12:18,890
Here, sir.

252
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:19,720
I don't smoke!

253
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,770
Just take it anyway.

254
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:22,510
Take it.

255
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:23,500
Take it.

256
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,450
This gentleman is right.

257
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,860
To defend the country,

258
00:12:28,010 --> 00:12:29,200
you risk your lives,

259
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:31,340
so we have to provide the meat.

260
00:12:31,410 --> 00:12:33,110
Isn't it written on the slogan outside?

261
00:12:33,110 --> 00:12:34,950
Everyone is responsible
for the destiny of the country,

262
00:12:34,950 --> 00:12:36,340
including the cooks.

263
00:12:37,210 --> 00:12:38,410
Including the cooks.

264
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:43,220
Don't be angry, sirs.

265
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:45,100
You just want meat, right?

266
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:47,090
No problem.

267
00:12:52,060 --> 00:12:53,110
No problem.

268
00:12:54,330 --> 00:12:55,460
No problem.

269
00:12:56,510 --> 00:12:58,270
You just want meat, right?

270
00:12:58,290 --> 00:12:59,080
How would the manager know

271
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,530
if there's meat?

272
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:00,930
Right.

273
00:13:00,930 --> 00:13:02,600
It's the cooks who know.

274
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:03,710
There is meat.

275
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:04,800
There is meat.

276
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:06,200
I promise there's meat.

277
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,470
It's coming right up.

278
00:13:07,490 --> 00:13:09,250
Gentlemen, have some snacks first.

279
00:13:09,250 --> 00:13:10,290
The meat is coming right up.

280
00:13:10,290 --> 00:13:11,490
Officer, please sit.

281
00:13:11,880 --> 00:13:13,200
The meat is coming right up.

282
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,310
The meat is coming right up.

283
00:13:14,310 --> 00:13:15,660
Have a seat.

284
00:13:15,680 --> 00:13:16,340
Please sit.

285
00:13:21,290 --> 00:13:22,540
Have some snacks first.

286
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:24,240
The meat is coming right up.

287
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,080
Please wait a moment.

288
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,100
Please wait a moment.

289
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:26,830
We want beef!

290
00:13:28,020 --> 00:13:29,080
It must be beef.

291
00:13:30,390 --> 00:13:31,380
And soup?

292
00:13:32,820 --> 00:13:34,080
They'll be served all together.

293
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:34,880
All together.

294
00:13:42,380 --> 00:13:43,350
Brat!

295
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:44,810
You startled me.

296
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:47,810
The beef I bought just this morning

297
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:49,100
was gone by noon.

298
00:13:49,390 --> 00:13:51,250
Did you steal it, you little brat?

299
00:13:51,270 --> 00:13:52,740
Manager, how is that possible?

300
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:55,050
You even took my cigarettes to treat them.

301
00:13:55,050 --> 00:13:55,910
Give me my cigarettes.

302
00:13:55,910 --> 00:13:56,780
I don't have any.

303
00:13:56,780 --> 00:13:57,570
You don't?

304
00:13:58,150 --> 00:13:58,950
Don't move.

305
00:13:59,060 --> 00:14:00,290
You didn't take them, huh?

306
00:14:00,290 --> 00:14:00,960
There's no more.

307
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:02,010
No more.

308
00:14:02,030 --> 00:14:02,600
Look.

309
00:14:02,850 --> 00:14:03,480
There's more.

310
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:03,890
There's no more.

311
00:14:03,890 --> 00:14:05,120
Turn around.

312
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:06,470
There's really no more.

313
00:14:07,780 --> 00:14:09,630
You hid quite a lot.

314
00:14:09,660 --> 00:14:10,350
You brat.

315
00:14:10,370 --> 00:14:11,970
I wasn't treating them.

316
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:13,130
I was helping you out of a jam.

317
00:14:13,130 --> 00:14:14,370
I deserve these.

318
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:15,530
Now you've taken them all.

319
00:14:15,530 --> 00:14:17,170
Search me. There's nothing left.

320
00:14:17,170 --> 00:14:18,080
Turn around again.

321
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:18,960
Turn around.

322
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:20,980
What is this?

323
00:14:21,050 --> 00:14:22,370
Manager, Manager, Manager.

324
00:14:22,370 --> 00:14:23,200
You can't touch here.

325
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,200
You can't touch here.

326
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:24,960
I'll show you.

327
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:25,800
I'll show you.

328
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:26,910
Show me.

329
00:14:26,940 --> 00:14:28,140
I'll show you.

330
00:14:29,830 --> 00:14:32,800
This is the money I've saved for 3 years
for my marriage.

331
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:34,130
I have nothing besides this.

332
00:14:34,130 --> 00:14:35,190
Come on, search me.

333
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:35,840
Do it.

334
00:14:35,870 --> 00:14:36,660
I won't.

335
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:38,860
The beef is gone anyway.

336
00:14:38,890 --> 00:14:40,780
Weren't you playing the generous guy?

337
00:14:40,780 --> 00:14:42,600
I'll just use the beef prepared

338
00:14:42,630 --> 00:14:43,530
for tomorrow's banquet.

339
00:14:43,530 --> 00:14:43,980
Xi.

340
00:14:44,010 --> 00:14:44,650
Don't!

341
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:45,230
Did you hear me?

342
00:14:45,230 --> 00:14:45,650
Don't.

343
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:46,480
Take his meat and...

344
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,590
Don't you get involved.

345
00:14:47,590 --> 00:14:48,120
Get lost!

346
00:14:48,130 --> 00:14:49,290
Get out of the way!

347
00:14:50,650 --> 00:14:51,320
Come on, Manager.

348
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,130
If you do this,

349
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:53,620
you might as well cut me up.

350
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:54,270
Come on.

351
00:14:54,290 --> 00:14:54,930
Come on.

352
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,440
What's the use of cutting you up?

353
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:58,280
Those people up front are still waiting.

354
00:14:58,280 --> 00:14:59,540
What are we going to do?

355
00:15:00,110 --> 00:15:01,710
I've already figured it out.

356
00:15:05,410 --> 00:15:06,170
What's this?

357
00:15:07,290 --> 00:15:08,650
Those soldiers

358
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:11,370
have definitely never tried
the Castanopsis tofu.

359
00:15:11,370 --> 00:15:13,410
I'll cut this Castanopsis tofu
into slices,

360
00:15:13,410 --> 00:15:15,750
then fry it thoroughly in oil,

361
00:15:15,770 --> 00:15:17,290
until it's crispy and wrinkled.

362
00:15:17,290 --> 00:15:19,010
Then I'll add some chili and beef tallow,

363
00:15:19,010 --> 00:15:20,370
and the tofu flavor will be gone.

364
00:15:20,370 --> 00:15:21,800
Then we tell them it's beef;

365
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:24,200
they won't be able
to taste the difference.

366
00:15:24,270 --> 00:15:25,380
Can you make it?

367
00:15:25,410 --> 00:15:26,600
When it's done later,

368
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,860
you can taste it first.

369
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:28,790
Okay.

370
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:31,410
Do as you said.

371
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,910
Keep your hands clean!

372
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:39,250
-Manager.
-Manager.

373
00:15:39,250 --> 00:15:40,960
We are innocent.

374
00:15:40,990 --> 00:15:41,840
You guys.

375
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:44,440
Manager.

376
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:45,080
Miss Xiaoyue.

377
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,170
Have some wedding candies.

378
00:15:46,170 --> 00:15:47,350
Remember to come tomorrow.

379
00:15:46,990 --> 00:15:49,620
[Han Xiaoyue]

380
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:48,460
Of course.

381
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:49,810
Congratulations.

382
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:57,260
Sikui, here, have some candies.

383
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,410
-Congratulations.
-Come tomorrow.

384
00:15:58,410 --> 00:15:59,260
Congratulations, Miss Xiaoyue.

385
00:15:59,260 --> 00:15:59,900
Thank you.

386
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:01,880
Erwa, have some candies.

387
00:16:02,370 --> 00:16:02,830
Thank you.

388
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:03,320
Come tomorrow.

389
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,200
Congratulations.

390
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:04,930
Li.

391
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:06,420
Okay, thank you, Xiaoyue.

392
00:16:06,530 --> 00:16:07,320
Here.

393
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:08,650
Xiaoyue, you're here?

394
00:16:08,650 --> 00:16:09,710
Congratulations.

395
00:16:10,370 --> 00:16:11,260
Buns.

396
00:16:12,030 --> 00:16:12,720
You must all come tomorrow.

397
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:13,800
-Every single one of you.
-Of course.

398
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:15,080
Here, have some candies.

399
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:16,670
So pretty and diligent.

400
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:17,560
Thank you, Miss Xiaoyue.

401
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:19,370
I wonder what good deeds Wanfu did
in his past life

402
00:16:19,370 --> 00:16:20,830
to have such good fortune.

403
00:16:21,530 --> 00:16:22,970
Brothers, when

404
00:16:23,070 --> 00:16:24,170
do you think I can marry

405
00:16:24,170 --> 00:16:25,220
such a girl?

406
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,130
You?

407
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:28,910
You'll never marry one.

408
00:16:28,910 --> 00:16:30,320
You sure have a sweet mouth.

409
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:32,500
I'll reward you with two more cups
of wedding wine tomorrow.

410
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,420
It's a deal.

411
00:16:34,890 --> 00:16:36,290
Didn't you go to do the anti-Japanese

412
00:16:36,290 --> 00:16:38,130
benefit performance with Miss Yu?

413
00:16:38,130 --> 00:16:39,640
Why did you come back so soon?

414
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:41,070
After the performance,

415
00:16:41,370 --> 00:16:43,210
Young Master Luo took Her Ladyship away.

416
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:44,530
They went on a date,

417
00:16:44,530 --> 00:16:45,740
so I came back.

418
00:16:46,140 --> 00:16:46,830
Here.

419
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:52,930
Is it sweet?

420
00:16:53,070 --> 00:16:53,790
Yes.

421
00:16:54,620 --> 00:16:55,940
I'll go clean up then.

422
00:16:59,090 --> 00:16:59,850
Come back.

423
00:17:08,829 --> 00:17:09,760
Open your mouth.

424
00:17:17,890 --> 00:17:18,690
Tastes good?

425
00:17:21,859 --> 00:17:22,660
No.

426
00:17:31,190 --> 00:17:34,240
[Nanjing]

427
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:44,350
[The Gentleman Is Not a Vessel]

428
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,160
I wrote

429
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:52,360
[Each Twig and Leaf Reflects Care]

430
00:17:49,010 --> 00:17:50,810
these words specially for you.

431
00:17:52,060 --> 00:17:54,120
Do you remember where they came from?

432
00:17:54,320 --> 00:17:55,810
"Each twig and leaf reflects care."

433
00:17:55,810 --> 00:17:56,720
Zheng Banqiao's

434
00:17:56,720 --> 00:17:58,330
"Painting Bamboo in the Weixian Office

435
00:17:58,330 --> 00:17:59,850
and Presenting It to Uncle Bao Kuo."

436
00:17:59,850 --> 00:18:01,710
You want me to keep my duty in mind,

437
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:03,040
no matter when and where,

438
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:05,900
always bearing in mind
the suffering of the people.

439
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:06,830
Good.

440
00:18:11,170 --> 00:18:12,410
Come out, Yujiao.

441
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:14,440
I saw you a long time ago.

442
00:18:17,190 --> 00:18:17,810
Father.

443
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:27,850
Go and

444
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:30,410
have a good talk with Yujiao.

445
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:32,740
It hasn't been easy for her.

446
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:41,220
I almost forgot it.

447
00:18:42,670 --> 00:18:43,430
Father.

448
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:45,960
It's specifically for your joint pain.

449
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:47,600
Sir!

450
00:18:52,410 --> 00:18:53,720
Brigade Commander, urgent order
from the Division Headquarters.

451
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:54,850
Please return to your unit immediately.

452
00:18:54,850 --> 00:18:56,580
The troops will set off at once.

453
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:20,300
Father.

454
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:23,340
I'm going to war.

455
00:20:10,130 --> 00:20:11,020
Mrs. Liu!

456
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:12,960
Mrs. Liu!

457
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:15,170
Mrs. Liu!

458
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:17,090
Mrs. Liu!

459
00:20:18,130 --> 00:20:19,130
Mrs. Liu, help me!

460
00:20:19,220 --> 00:20:19,960
Coming!

461
00:20:19,990 --> 00:20:21,390
Help me! Hurry up!

462
00:20:21,610 --> 00:20:22,540
He's not eating?

463
00:20:22,730 --> 00:20:23,850
Take it easy.

464
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:24,700
Come on.

465
00:20:27,690 --> 00:20:28,890
Let me pour it for you.

466
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:30,020
-Pour it in.
-No rush.

467
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:31,260
Okay, here.

468
00:20:31,350 --> 00:20:32,270
Pour it in.

469
00:20:33,050 --> 00:20:34,350
It's 622 pieces, right?

470
00:20:34,350 --> 00:20:35,610
Yes, they're all here.

471
00:20:39,590 --> 00:20:43,130
[Understanding Water, Honoring Mountain]

472
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:48,270
[Lofty Pavilion Reaching the Cloud]

473
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:03,400
Here's one more.

474
00:21:06,460 --> 00:21:07,260
It's raining!

475
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:08,720
Madam, take an umbrella!

476
00:21:09,100 --> 00:21:11,760
Madam, you're pregnant.
Be careful not to slip!

477
00:24:03,350 --> 00:24:04,550
Eat something first.

478
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:05,980
I made you some egg tea.

479
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:07,390
It removes the internal heat.

480
00:24:07,390 --> 00:24:08,150
Come.

481
00:24:09,560 --> 00:24:10,360
What's wrong?

482
00:24:13,650 --> 00:24:15,650
Look at my invention.

483
00:24:18,260 --> 00:24:19,260
It's a mechanism?

484
00:24:20,120 --> 00:24:21,150
Is it sturdy?

485
00:24:21,170 --> 00:24:22,020
Try it.

486
00:24:27,480 --> 00:24:29,210
It can actually work like this?

487
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:32,480
What are you wearing tomorrow?

488
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:33,880
Should I borrow Young Master Luo's
student uniform

489
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:35,190
from Her Ladyship?

490
00:24:35,320 --> 00:24:37,030
I've already paid the deposit
for the mandarin jacket.

491
00:24:37,030 --> 00:24:38,590
I'll go pick it up in a bit.

492
00:24:39,090 --> 00:24:39,760
Besides,

493
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:42,000
no groom wears a student uniform.

494
00:24:43,260 --> 00:24:44,060
Han Xiaoyue,

495
00:24:44,670 --> 00:24:46,690
you just like students, don't you?

496
00:24:47,090 --> 00:24:49,200
Why are you saying this?

497
00:24:49,410 --> 00:24:52,200
I just like people who are literate.

498
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,650
Literate?

499
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:56,900
We aren't even married yet,

500
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:59,900
and you already mind
that I don't know many words?

501
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:04,290
[Wedding]

502
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:01,500
Let me tell you,

503
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:04,760
even though I don't know many words,

504
00:25:05,930 --> 00:25:07,690
I bought you a gold hairpin.

505
00:25:14,210 --> 00:25:15,340
It's amazing.

506
00:25:15,360 --> 00:25:16,180
Wanfu.

507
00:25:16,890 --> 00:25:18,070
I heard

508
00:25:18,570 --> 00:25:21,000
the Japanese army
has arrived on the Huangpu River.

509
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:22,800
Is there really going to be a war?

510
00:25:22,930 --> 00:25:24,950
Can we still hold our wedding banquet?

511
00:25:24,950 --> 00:25:26,720
Why are you worrying about this?

512
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:28,120
The higher-ups are like,

513
00:25:28,220 --> 00:25:30,760
"It's a critical moment,

514
00:25:31,430 --> 00:25:33,190
and war is inevitable."

515
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:35,190
But by night,

516
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:36,680
they changed their tune.

517
00:25:37,650 --> 00:25:40,580
"There's still a glimmer
of hope for peace,

518
00:25:40,650 --> 00:25:42,080
and we won't give up."

519
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:45,260
They talk like flipping pancakes,

520
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:47,200
first one side, then the other.

521
00:25:47,230 --> 00:25:49,330
They're not even as credible
as a cook like me.

522
00:25:49,330 --> 00:25:50,200
Don't worry.

523
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:52,770
If the sky falls,
the tall ones will hold it up.

524
00:25:53,850 --> 00:25:56,180
We ordinary folks
have no say in it anyway.

525
00:25:58,480 --> 00:25:59,210
Give it to me.

526
00:26:03,810 --> 00:26:04,670
Wash your face.

527
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,090
Washing my face isn't important.

528
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:09,050
There's no rush.

529
00:26:09,650 --> 00:26:11,280
I want to try

530
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:13,760
Miss Han's invention.

531
00:26:22,650 --> 00:26:23,580
So comfortable.

532
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:24,800
Xiaoyue.

533
00:26:26,370 --> 00:26:29,330
Here in Shanghai,

534
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:32,560
we can say we finally have a home.

535
00:26:37,100 --> 00:26:38,180
Miss Han,

536
00:26:39,890 --> 00:26:41,790
please come quickly

537
00:26:41,810 --> 00:26:43,500
to Mr. Meng,

538
00:26:43,520 --> 00:26:45,720
who can afford a gold hairpin.

539
00:26:49,090 --> 00:26:50,560
Come on. Come on.

540
00:27:05,990 --> 00:27:06,590
Here we go.

541
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:14,170
Over how many provinces
does the crescent moon shine?

542
00:27:14,200 --> 00:27:18,570
Which families are happy, which are sad?

543
00:27:18,700 --> 00:27:23,280
Which couples share the same bed?

544
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:27,750
Which ones are scattered apart?

545
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:29,890
Fight to the end!

546
00:27:29,890 --> 00:27:32,080
United as one!

547
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:32,560
Beat...

548
00:27:32,650 --> 00:27:34,810
Congratulations, sir.

549
00:27:34,930 --> 00:27:36,090
Victory in the War of Resistance
is certain!

550
00:27:36,090 --> 00:27:37,030
You startled me.

551
00:27:37,140 --> 00:27:38,250
I have no spare money.

552
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:39,650
[Divination]

553
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,760
I, Half-Immortal Huang,
have traveled all over the land,

554
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:42,280
relying on my knowledge
of the stars above,

555
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:43,030
[Divination]

556
00:27:42,280 --> 00:27:43,280
the earth below,

557
00:27:43,410 --> 00:27:44,810
mastering the universe,

558
00:27:44,930 --> 00:27:46,200
balancing yin and yang—

559
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:47,300
but never on money.

560
00:27:47,340 --> 00:27:48,510
I'll give you three sentences

561
00:27:48,510 --> 00:27:49,740
for free.

562
00:27:49,820 --> 00:27:56,700
[Divination]

563
00:27:51,090 --> 00:27:53,750
Sir, a very joyful occasion
is coming up for you.

564
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:56,400
I have a joyful occasion coming up,
and so do you.

565
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:57,890
There are plenty of people on this street
with joyful occasions coming up.

566
00:27:57,890 --> 00:27:59,170
I can read fortunes too.

567
00:27:59,170 --> 00:28:01,960
Sir, you have a lady on your mind.

568
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,490
A lady from Anhui.

569
00:28:11,610 --> 00:28:13,830
Sir, you lack a bit of literary talent,

570
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,770
and you make a living with your craft.

571
00:28:14,020 --> 00:28:15,700
[Huang Ziming]

572
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:22,570
That doesn't count.

573
00:28:22,620 --> 00:28:24,280
There's still one left. Go on.

574
00:28:24,960 --> 00:28:26,750
The lowest level of divination
looks at bones,

575
00:28:26,750 --> 00:28:28,570
the middle at complexion,

576
00:28:28,610 --> 00:28:30,280
and the highest at voice.

577
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:33,930
Sir, your voice is fiery,

578
00:28:33,930 --> 00:28:35,120
so you run around without support.

579
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:36,850
And your jue note is out of tune.

580
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:40,220
Although you're rushing toward
a great joy now,

581
00:28:40,330 --> 00:28:43,120
you're unaware of an impending disaster.

582
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:46,090
You're destined for imprisonment.

583
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,370
I'm telling you,

584
00:28:52,390 --> 00:28:53,760
if you had met me yesterday

585
00:28:53,760 --> 00:28:54,960
and said something like this,

586
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,760
I would've slapped you already.

587
00:28:56,890 --> 00:28:57,950
Stop following me.

588
00:28:59,200 --> 00:28:59,930
Sir!

589
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:02,040
For us to meet today—

590
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:02,370
Let's go.

591
00:29:02,370 --> 00:29:03,930
That's fate!

592
00:29:04,090 --> 00:29:06,840
So I must help you resolve this crisis.

593
00:29:07,330 --> 00:29:09,240
If I'm not wrong,

594
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:10,720
the items in your bag

595
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:14,410
must be the clothes for your wedding,
right?

596
00:29:16,330 --> 00:29:17,330
Am I right?

597
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:19,850
Gold...

598
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:21,810
Gold, wood, water, fire...

599
00:29:21,930 --> 00:29:23,280
Fire, wood, gold...

600
00:29:25,330 --> 00:29:29,600
And there's jewelry for a lady.

601
00:29:29,730 --> 00:29:30,560
You brat.

602
00:29:31,310 --> 00:29:33,680
You've been following me
all the way, haven't you?

603
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:36,700
Everything in your life is predestined.

604
00:29:38,030 --> 00:29:40,680
However, sir, your voice is resonant.

605
00:29:40,870 --> 00:29:43,100
This crisis can still be resolved.

606
00:29:44,960 --> 00:29:46,910
You must first pray to Lord Guan.

607
00:29:48,650 --> 00:29:49,650
Pray to Lord Guan?

608
00:29:50,470 --> 00:29:52,570
Then I have to make a donation, right?

609
00:29:53,280 --> 00:29:54,040
Alright.

610
00:30:00,650 --> 00:30:02,070
You're not blind, huh?

611
00:30:04,890 --> 00:30:05,750
Let me tell you.

612
00:30:05,750 --> 00:30:08,250
I don't believe in fate.

613
00:30:08,370 --> 00:30:09,720
I only believe in money.

614
00:30:09,910 --> 00:30:11,040
If I had believed you,

615
00:30:11,040 --> 00:30:13,050
I would have changed my fate long ago.

616
00:30:13,050 --> 00:30:14,030
Don't bother me again,

617
00:30:14,030 --> 00:30:15,160
or I'll really slap you.

618
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:16,050
Get lost!

619
00:30:17,100 --> 00:30:19,060
A gentleman doesn't stand
under a dangerous wall!

620
00:30:19,060 --> 00:30:21,440
If you don't listen to me,
you'll suffer a disaster!

621
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:22,170
Who are you?

622
00:30:24,850 --> 00:30:25,680
Let go of me!

623
00:30:27,150 --> 00:30:27,800
Kill!

624
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:28,570
One!

625
00:30:28,610 --> 00:30:29,280
Kill!

626
00:30:29,370 --> 00:30:29,960
Two!

627
00:30:30,040 --> 00:30:30,850
Kill!

628
00:30:30,880 --> 00:30:31,470
One!

629
00:30:31,610 --> 00:30:32,290
Kill!

630
00:30:34,370 --> 00:30:35,040
Everyone, get out of the car!

631
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:35,760
Get out of the car!

632
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:36,280
Get out of the car!

633
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:38,200
Those in the carriage,
hurry up and get in!

634
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:38,760
Go!

635
00:30:38,790 --> 00:30:40,790
What are you looking at? Get inside!

636
00:30:41,370 --> 00:30:41,960
Get down!

637
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:42,510
Officer...

638
00:30:42,510 --> 00:30:43,370
Get out of here!

639
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:51,280
Go inside!

640
00:30:51,390 --> 00:30:52,600
Go! Hurry up!

641
00:30:56,530 --> 00:30:57,340
Hurry!

642
00:30:58,090 --> 00:30:59,130
Move it!

643
00:31:00,500 --> 00:31:02,280
-Do you want to die?
-Go! Go!

644
00:31:02,330 --> 00:31:03,200
Behave yourself!

645
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:04,330
Officer! Officer!

646
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:05,410
Let me out.

647
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:06,440
Behave yourself!

648
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:07,280
Officer!

649
00:31:07,330 --> 00:31:07,810
Officer!

650
00:31:07,810 --> 00:31:08,410
Officer!

651
00:31:08,480 --> 00:31:09,470
Stay put!

652
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:11,060
Officer!

653
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:12,240
What's going on, officer?

654
00:31:12,240 --> 00:31:13,810
You brought us here for no reason!

655
00:31:13,810 --> 00:31:15,080
Let me out!

656
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:20,410
Officer, officer.

657
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:21,520
Let me out.

658
00:31:50,170 --> 00:31:51,090
Yueming,

659
00:31:51,890 --> 00:31:52,760
this day

660
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:56,170
was August 13, 1937.

661
00:31:57,680 --> 00:32:00,240
The Japanese Army started
to mass its naval, ground, and air forces

662
00:32:00,240 --> 00:32:02,240
to attack Shanghai.

663
00:32:02,240 --> 00:32:04,650
The Chinese army rose in resistance.

664
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:07,520
The Battle of Shanghai broke out.

665
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:09,860
That night,

666
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:13,100
you kicked Mommy's belly
with your little feet.

667
00:32:13,230 --> 00:32:14,620
Mommy was worried about

668
00:32:14,650 --> 00:32:17,280
your father
who was heading to the battlefield.

669
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:18,560
Auntie Xiaoyue

670
00:32:18,580 --> 00:32:21,310
was still looking forward
to her lively wedding.

671
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:25,040
The cruel war struck

672
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:27,430
and destroyed all of this.

673
00:32:35,540 --> 00:32:37,130
Change the time in the records.

674
00:32:37,130 --> 00:32:38,050
Just say

675
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:39,960
they were previously recruited
at the station.

676
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:41,490
Anyone who talks too much
will be skinned alive.

677
00:32:41,490 --> 00:32:42,250
Step back!

678
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:49,730
Everyone, eyes right!

679
00:32:52,110 --> 00:32:53,450
You all know these words, right?

680
00:32:53,450 --> 00:32:55,780
Join forces in the nation's time of peril!

681
00:32:55,810 --> 00:32:56,960
I won't waste words.

682
00:32:57,540 --> 00:32:59,640
The Japanese
are already attacking Shanghai.

683
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:01,220
Our unit is understaffed

684
00:33:01,250 --> 00:33:02,710
and needs more personnel.

685
00:33:02,830 --> 00:33:05,800
This is a great opportunity
for you to serve the country.

686
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:07,650
Those who stay and serve faithfully

687
00:33:07,650 --> 00:33:09,720
will each receive 5 yuan
as a settlement allowance.

688
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:11,440
You'll have enough to eat every meal.

689
00:33:11,440 --> 00:33:13,170
From now on, we are brothers.

690
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:15,770
But let me make one thing clear first.

691
00:33:16,120 --> 00:33:17,330
If anyone

692
00:33:17,650 --> 00:33:18,650
tries to trick me

693
00:33:18,940 --> 00:33:19,910
or run away,

694
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:21,680
don't blame me for...

695
00:33:23,330 --> 00:33:24,330
What is that?

696
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:26,720
Why are you holding a banner
inside the room?

697
00:33:26,720 --> 00:33:27,760
What a bad omen!

698
00:33:30,870 --> 00:33:33,200
Join forces in the nation's time of peril!

699
00:33:33,280 --> 00:33:35,480
I've had this intention for a long time.

700
00:33:37,480 --> 00:33:38,430
Sir,

701
00:33:38,450 --> 00:33:40,990
your face is glowing,
and your forehead looks radiant.

702
00:33:40,990 --> 00:33:42,890
You will surely have great luck soon.

703
00:33:42,890 --> 00:33:44,040
Let me see your left hand.

704
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:45,230
How old are you?

705
00:33:54,620 --> 00:33:55,470
Don't move.

706
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:00,850
It's fake?

707
00:34:01,710 --> 00:34:02,520
Don't move.

708
00:34:11,659 --> 00:34:13,580
You, join forces in the back.

709
00:34:15,810 --> 00:34:16,690
Distribute the uniforms.

710
00:34:16,690 --> 00:34:17,360
-Yes.
-Yes.

711
00:34:21,480 --> 00:34:22,130
Yours.

712
00:34:23,060 --> 00:34:23,850
Take it!

713
00:34:24,679 --> 00:34:26,320
I won't wear this stupid outfit!

714
00:34:26,320 --> 00:34:27,520
I won't join the army!

715
00:34:27,560 --> 00:34:28,370
This is called forced conscription.

716
00:34:28,370 --> 00:34:29,300
Do you know that?

717
00:34:29,370 --> 00:34:30,409
Stop yelling!

718
00:34:30,560 --> 00:34:31,409
Come on, you...

719
00:34:31,409 --> 00:34:33,409
What you're doing is worse than bandits.

720
00:34:33,409 --> 00:34:34,560
When bandits kidnap people,

721
00:34:34,560 --> 00:34:36,420
they at least give them a warning.

722
00:34:36,850 --> 00:34:38,100
A warning, huh?

723
00:34:38,130 --> 00:34:39,090
I'll kill...

724
00:34:44,810 --> 00:34:45,750
Company Commander,

725
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:46,770
isn't this the guy who used tofu

726
00:34:46,770 --> 00:34:48,000
to trick us?

727
00:34:48,100 --> 00:34:48,889
Look at him.

728
00:34:51,560 --> 00:34:52,210
Look.

729
00:34:52,870 --> 00:34:53,929
Stand up straight.

730
00:34:56,449 --> 00:34:57,450
An acquaintance.

731
00:34:58,220 --> 00:34:59,050
Let me ask you,

732
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:01,950
how did you make tofu

733
00:35:01,970 --> 00:35:03,740
taste like beef?

734
00:35:04,080 --> 00:35:05,730
I really thought it was beef.

735
00:35:06,160 --> 00:35:07,770
But then I realized,

736
00:35:08,110 --> 00:35:10,810
we brothers spent money on beef

737
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:12,560
but ate your tofu!

738
00:35:14,690 --> 00:35:16,330
Sir! Sir! I...

739
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:17,980
It was a misunderstanding!

740
00:35:18,080 --> 00:35:19,250
The Manager didn't provide meat.

741
00:35:19,250 --> 00:35:21,080
I'm just a cook,
I couldn't call the shots.

742
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:21,810
Right?

743
00:35:21,850 --> 00:35:22,560
How about this?

744
00:35:22,560 --> 00:35:24,460
I'll invite you to my wedding feast, okay?

745
00:35:24,460 --> 00:35:25,940
I'm getting married tomorrow.

746
00:35:25,940 --> 00:35:27,000
I'll invite you to my wedding feast.

747
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:28,120
I beg you, have mercy.

748
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:29,030
Please let me go.

749
00:35:29,030 --> 00:35:30,160
Please let me go.

750
00:35:31,370 --> 00:35:32,100
Oh, right.

751
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:35,120
"Everyone is responsible
for the destiny of the country,

752
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:37,130
including the cooks."

753
00:35:37,410 --> 00:35:38,870
You said that, didn't you?

754
00:35:38,890 --> 00:35:40,020
Then let me tell you,

755
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:41,840
you'll have no choice

756
00:35:43,030 --> 00:35:44,160
but to join the army.

757
00:35:44,880 --> 00:35:45,680
Take it!

758
00:35:46,120 --> 00:35:49,230
Sir, we don't want
to join the army either!

759
00:35:49,560 --> 00:35:51,490
I'm just a primary school teacher!

760
00:35:52,410 --> 00:35:53,040
Sir,

761
00:35:53,080 --> 00:35:54,030
please spare us!

762
00:35:55,210 --> 00:35:56,290
Sir, please.

763
00:35:56,370 --> 00:35:57,560
I can't fight in a war.

764
00:35:57,560 --> 00:35:58,640
Why don't you understand

765
00:35:58,640 --> 00:36:01,040
what I'm saying?

766
00:36:01,290 --> 00:36:03,920
I don't want to join the army!

767
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:06,320
I'm going back to get married tomorrow.

768
00:36:08,040 --> 00:36:08,850
He's pissed.

769
00:36:10,880 --> 00:36:11,940
Give him a massage.

770
00:36:12,600 --> 00:36:13,660
Don't hit his face.

771
00:36:13,730 --> 00:36:14,440
Okay!

772
00:36:14,570 --> 00:36:15,130
Move!

773
00:36:15,150 --> 00:36:16,120
What are you doing?

774
00:36:16,120 --> 00:36:18,290
-Wait! What are you doing?
-Behave yourself! Let's go!

775
00:36:18,290 --> 00:36:19,480
What are you doing?

776
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:21,250
What are you looking at?

777
00:36:24,850 --> 00:36:26,040
Join the army or get married?

778
00:36:26,040 --> 00:36:26,870
Get married!

779
00:36:28,250 --> 00:36:29,930
Join the army or get married?

780
00:36:30,270 --> 00:36:31,210
Get married!

781
00:36:34,180 --> 00:36:35,920
Join the army or get married?

782
00:36:36,010 --> 00:36:37,060
Get married!

783
00:36:38,050 --> 00:36:38,840
Everyone,

784
00:36:40,240 --> 00:36:41,680
eyes right!

785
00:36:45,590 --> 00:36:46,630
What did you see?

786
00:36:46,810 --> 00:36:47,580
Nothing.

787
00:36:48,550 --> 00:36:49,740
Nothing.

788
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:50,820
We saw nothing.

789
00:36:52,560 --> 00:36:53,930
I saw them hitting him.

790
00:36:54,950 --> 00:36:56,000
Good eyesight.

791
00:36:57,730 --> 00:36:59,380
You're the one who saw it, right?

792
00:36:59,380 --> 00:36:59,980
Come here!

793
00:36:59,990 --> 00:37:01,060
What are you doing?

794
00:37:01,080 --> 00:37:02,140
What are you doing?

795
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:03,750
Stand up straight!

796
00:37:04,170 --> 00:37:05,070
How dare you hit us!

797
00:37:05,070 --> 00:37:05,970
You saw it, huh?

798
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:07,660
You can ask us to join the army,

799
00:37:08,530 --> 00:37:09,790
but you can't bully us!

800
00:37:10,270 --> 00:37:10,920
Everyone!

801
00:37:10,940 --> 00:37:11,960
What right do you have to hit me?

802
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:14,050
Eyes right!

803
00:37:16,420 --> 00:37:17,380
Cut the crap!

804
00:37:17,740 --> 00:37:18,760
What did you see?

805
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:21,700
Nothing.

806
00:37:21,730 --> 00:37:22,480
Wrong.

807
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:23,920
You saw it.

808
00:37:24,430 --> 00:37:27,900
This is called a massage.

809
00:37:27,970 --> 00:37:28,820
Understand?

810
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:31,000
Understood.

811
00:37:31,030 --> 00:37:32,110
What did you see?

812
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:34,210
A massage.

813
00:37:34,240 --> 00:37:34,990
Louder!

814
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:37,480
A massage!

815
00:37:38,190 --> 00:37:39,060
Good boys.

816
00:37:39,410 --> 00:37:40,290
That's enough.

817
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:41,500
Don't kill him.

818
00:37:42,900 --> 00:37:43,700
Pull him here.

819
00:37:43,730 --> 00:37:44,490
Move!

820
00:37:44,520 --> 00:37:45,650
Come on!

821
00:37:49,360 --> 00:37:50,030
Go!

822
00:37:58,120 --> 00:38:00,140
Is a cook responsible for the destiny
of the country?

823
00:38:00,140 --> 00:38:00,930
Yes.

824
00:38:01,430 --> 00:38:03,030
Join the army or get married?

825
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:05,430
Join the army.

826
00:38:06,140 --> 00:38:06,970
Name.

827
00:38:08,420 --> 00:38:09,420
Kong Erbao.

828
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:10,640
Register!

829
00:38:12,660 --> 00:38:13,490
At ease.

830
00:38:15,530 --> 00:38:16,890
Eyes right!

831
00:38:18,440 --> 00:38:19,770
Eyes right!

832
00:38:22,090 --> 00:38:23,210
Look forward!

833
00:38:24,810 --> 00:38:26,000
Fuchen, how have you been?

834
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:27,300
Is your family doing well?

835
00:38:27,300 --> 00:38:29,800
All well. Thank you for asking,
Brigade Commander.

836
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:30,640
Salute!

837
00:38:35,030 --> 00:38:36,710
I've been happy for days since I heard

838
00:38:36,710 --> 00:38:38,410
you were assigned to the 87th Brigade.

839
00:38:38,410 --> 00:38:39,750
Regimental Commander Liu
and Regimental Commander Feng

840
00:38:39,750 --> 00:38:41,080
even planned to line up to welcome you.

841
00:38:41,080 --> 00:38:41,930
I didn't expect you...

842
00:38:41,930 --> 00:38:42,960
Don't say anything yet.

843
00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:44,490
I'll walk around by myself.

844
00:38:45,590 --> 00:38:46,200
Yes, sir.

845
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:52,720
Left turn! Right turn!

846
00:38:53,870 --> 00:38:55,270
Stop the drill!

847
00:38:55,290 --> 00:38:57,930
Everyone, take a 15-minute break!

848
00:39:07,740 --> 00:39:09,040
Hurry up! Water!

849
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:09,770
Hurry up!

850
00:39:10,250 --> 00:39:11,240
You are the only one in a hurry.

851
00:39:11,240 --> 00:39:12,320
Don't rush.

852
00:39:13,960 --> 00:39:15,560
What's the background
of our new brigade commander?

853
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:16,720
What did he do before?

854
00:39:16,720 --> 00:39:17,720
How old is he?

855
00:39:28,970 --> 00:39:32,130
♪ I walked you all the way
to the main road ♪

856
00:39:33,820 --> 00:39:38,430
♪ Don't be sad
about a temporary separation ♪

857
00:39:39,570 --> 00:39:44,520
♪ It doesn't matter if we can't
see each other for 2 or 3 years ♪

858
00:39:45,980 --> 00:39:50,950
♪ It's just that
when you're far away from home ♪

859
00:39:47,210 --> 00:39:48,160
Attention

860
00:39:52,350 --> 00:39:57,290
♪ You must take care of yourself ♪

861
00:39:58,810 --> 00:40:03,390
♪ Don't spread gossip ♪

862
00:40:05,330 --> 00:40:07,940
[To Save Our Nation, Fight to the End]

863
00:40:16,090 --> 00:40:18,370
[To Save Our Nation, Fight to the End]

864
00:40:52,080 --> 00:40:54,160
Recruit platoon, fall in immediately!

865
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:55,290
Check your puttees!

866
00:40:55,330 --> 00:40:56,910
Keep your heads clear!

867
00:40:56,940 --> 00:40:58,040
Erbao, what are you doing?

868
00:40:58,040 --> 00:40:58,960
Time to fall in. Let's go.

869
00:40:58,960 --> 00:40:59,690
Blindy!

870
00:41:00,330 --> 00:41:00,970
What?

871
00:41:02,490 --> 00:41:03,370
What happened?

872
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:05,080
The new commander will be here soon.

873
00:41:05,080 --> 00:41:05,480
Right.

874
00:41:05,510 --> 00:41:06,740
I just asked around.

875
00:41:06,810 --> 00:41:07,770
Our new brigade commander

876
00:41:07,770 --> 00:41:09,330
used to be a division chief of staff.

877
00:41:09,330 --> 00:41:10,120
He's well-educated.

878
00:41:10,120 --> 00:41:11,290
He's strict with military discipline,
meticulous in everything,

879
00:41:11,290 --> 00:41:12,000
and a tough guy.

880
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:12,640
Let's go.

881
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:15,890
The officers

882
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:17,330
must have all gone to the new commander

883
00:41:17,330 --> 00:41:18,660
to present themselves.

884
00:41:18,850 --> 00:41:19,810
This morning,

885
00:41:19,810 --> 00:41:21,440
I found a dog hole under the backyard wall

886
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:22,710
by the stables.

887
00:41:22,810 --> 00:41:24,770
There definitely
won't be any patrols there now.

888
00:41:24,770 --> 00:41:26,770
There's no better chance than this.

889
00:41:26,850 --> 00:41:27,780
What do you mean?

890
00:41:29,250 --> 00:41:30,670
Nothing ventured, nothing gained.

891
00:41:30,670 --> 00:41:31,650
Are you going with me?

892
00:41:31,650 --> 00:41:33,250
You are so smart, aren't you?

893
00:42:50,670 --> 00:42:51,730
What are you doing?

894
00:42:55,280 --> 00:42:56,170
Bring him over!

895
00:43:00,100 --> 00:43:00,810
Get out!
